An AP constable has been arrested for stealing a Solar Panel belonging to a resident of Oloosirikona in Mandera county. Constable Francis Wafula attached to Lafey, Mandera was arrested in Isinya, Kajiado County on SaturdayÂ evening. DCI boss George Kinoti said they were acting on an alarm raised by the victim that an unknown man had stormed into his compound and made away with the property. "DCI detectives rushed to his residence whereupon they arrested the Suspect and recovered the said Solar Panel from him," Kinoti said. Kinoti said Wafula will remain in Police custody awaiting arraignment for the offense of stealing.